From 08be1641a87fdbbdb84fde2202e654d77e721e22 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 20 Mar 2026 19:24:45 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix crash loop: handle null intent in FlipperBleService
 onStartCommand

When Android kills and restarts a START_STICKY service, it delivers a
null intent. The previous code only called startForeground() for the
ACTION_START_FOREGROUND action, so null-intent restarts never promoted
the service to foreground. On Android 12+ this triggers a
ForegroundServiceDidNotStartInTimeException after ~10 seconds, crashing
the app in a repeating loop.

The fix adds an else branch that calls startForeground() for any
unrecognized or null action, and returns START_NOT_STICKY for stop
requests to prevent unnecessary restarts.

https://claude.ai/code/session_01B9CtX7SJ6DDp6MkfBGUvCb
---
 .../java/com/vesper/flipper/ble/FlipperBleService.kt  | 11 ++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/app/src/main/java/com/vesper/flipper/ble/FlipperBleService.kt b/app/src/main/java/com/vesper/flipper/ble/FlipperBleService.kt
index 072a60b..16e0b9e 100644
--- a/app/src/main/java/com/vesper/flipper/ble/FlipperBleService.kt
+++ b/app/src/main/java/com/vesper/flipper/ble/FlipperBleService.kt
@@ -174,7 +174,16 @@ class FlipperBleService : Service() {
     override fun onStartCommand(intent: Intent?, flags: Int, startId: Int): Int {
         when (intent?.action) {
             ACTION_START_FOREGROUND -> startForegroundService()
-            ACTION_STOP -> stopSelf()
+            ACTION_STOP -> {
+                stopSelf()
+                return START_NOT_STICKY
+            }
+            else -> {
+                // START_STICKY restarts with a null intent after the system kills the
+                // service. We must call startForeground() promptly or Android 12+ will
+                // throw ForegroundServiceDidNotStartInTimeException and crash the app.
+                startForegroundService()
+            }
         }
         return START_STICKY
     }
